div.p:
The maps and atlases, esteemed friend, have been distributed according to your instructions.
Hochstetter & Petermann (1863). See A. Petermann to M, 27 April 1864 (in this edition as 64-04-27a). I shall try to procure the diaries and maps of Walker and Landsborough for you and enclose them with the next consignment. Meanwhile I have already sent you several others for your institute by various means. Proeschel has left Australia with his maps. I have not succeeded in securing an Apteryx;
The New Zealand Kiwi; for the request for one, see A. Petermann to M, 27 April 1864 (in this edition as 64-04-27a). however, I still have to send quite a few other things and can enclose this animal at a later date.

You were so kind as to send me several copies of newspapers by the last mail, and also several issues of your esteemed journal;


      Mittheilungen aus Justus Perthes geographischer Anstalt (ed. Petermann). M passed on items of interest to newspapers in Australia, particularly the German-language press in Melbourne, from the journal and from German newspapers sent by Petermann.
 relevant notes from these are always utilised here.
